<br>
That's a pretty strong opinion, Col.  I totally disagree with it.  I swear by Improved Reclaim, Elemental Pact, and Quick Summoning.  Many magicians value Mend Companion and Pet Discipline as well.  All of them are useful Class skills.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>doesn't IR defeat the point of reclaiming in the first place?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The answer to that depends on what you plan on using Improved Reclaim for.  I use it to recast and rebuff pets mana free.  What would you use it for, Xoran?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>however doesn't IR shift to a different formula where you get back something like 90 to 100% of the cost of the pet, which means you can't take advantage of the hp to mana disparity conversions that exists for regular reclaim?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It does shift to a different formula, but using maximim efficiency skills and effects allows you to &quot;pet canni&quot; anyway.  I use it a lot in PoP groups, to make sure I always have mana for the next pull.  I like to have 2 pets memmed (both Greater Vocarates) and alternate them. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A> at: 11/19/02 5:18:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 4:33:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=447.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: IR questions and answers</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It does shift to a different formula, but using maximim efficiency skills and effects allows you to &quot;pet canni&quot; anyway.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
