<br>
For example, when chaining pets, minimizing aggro is critical, as each new pet starts with zero hate, while the mage accumulates hate over time <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(although it does decay over time)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I used to alternate our DoTs with boots, and almost never get aggro chaining pets.  Anything stronger and I wound up getting chased with each new pet beyond the second one.  With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCS3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> though I could now use rains as my &quot;low aggro&quot; damage spell instead of dots.  Rains do much more damage and are much more mana efficient than our dots.<br>
<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Firebolt of Tallon</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, aggro becomes a much bigger limitation, but again, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCS3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I think helps a great deal.<br>
<br>
Just having more <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;slop&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when managing aggro seems quite worthwhile to me.<br>
